Root causes and direct fixes

Problem 1: Pasteboard flattening

The clipboard may provide:
	•	animated payload
	•	static raster preview

Fix:
	•	prefer animated payload UTI/MIME when available
	•	only fall back to raster preview if animated payload absent

Problem 2: Server-side normalization strips animation

The media service may be generating a PNG/JPEG thumbnail and handing that to the UI as the only asset.

Fix:
	•	preserve original asset reference in message payload
	•	attach preview separately

Problem 3: Wrong UI component

The chat cell may always use a static image view.

Fix:
	•	introduce AnimatedMediaCell
	•	bind it when is_animated == true

Problem 4: Performance concerns

Too many GIFs can tank scroll performance.

Fix:
	•	only animate visible cells
	•	pause offscreen
	•	transcode heavy GIFs
	•	cap simultaneous active animations

